{"title_page": "Minsan may isang puta", "text_new": "{{Infobox book\n| name          = Minsan may Isang Puta (short story)\n| image         =\n| caption       = \n| author        = Mike Portes\n| language      = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| genre         = [[Fictional biographies]]\n| published     = *April 30, 2004, Peyups.com\n* December, 2011 Mismo Magazine (U.A.E.)\n*July 16, 2012, The Dove Files<ref>{{cite book|last1=Portes|first1=Mike|title=The Dove Files |date=July 16, 2012|publisher=CreateSpace Publishing|isbn=978-1-4774-3185-6|page=136|url=https://www.amazon.com/The-Dove-Files-Mike-Portes/dp/1477431853}}</ref>\n*Nov 22, 2014, Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba pa\n<ref>{{cite book|last1=Portes|first1=Mike|title=Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba pa|date=November 22, 2014|publisher=CreateSpace Publishing|isbn=978-1-5031-3504-8|page=112|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/minsan-may-isang-puta-mike-portes/1120821316?ean=9781503135048}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Minsan may Isang Puta''' is an allegory in Filipino, written by Ms. Mike Portes <ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://hubo.asia/tag/minsan-may-isang-puta |title=Minsan May Isang Puta \u00ab HUBO Productions |publisher=Hubo.asia |date=2012-10-22 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> in 2004 and was modified in 2007.\n\n== Summary ==\nA woman bares her soul to her listener. As she shares her pain and unravels herself, she becomes more than the perceived prostitute but a survivor and a mother who is both familiar and forgotten.\n\n\"...a short piece that uses a first-person narrative technique that speaks directly to its reader. The voice is even pedestrian that in its familiar tone the reader is simply drawn to it. The voice simply asks that you listen as if an old friend or relative is about to tell a story. It is a story that found thousands of listening ears since it first appeared in 2004. The story is at once familiar yet enigmatic. In \u201cre-telling the truth through the words of a loving mother and by using sex as an impulse zone\u201d is perhaps what makes it fresh, intimate and endearing.'' (\"When Doves Cry\", October 22, 2012)<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n== Film Adaptation and Reception ==\n\n'''Minsan may Isang Puta''' won a film grant in 2010 in the [[multiperspectivity|multi-narrative]] indie film: \"Ganap na Babae\" (International title: Garden of Eve).\n\nMs. [[Mercedes Cabral]] in her role in the screenplay of \"Minsan may Isang Puta\" was praised by local media.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pinoyparazzi.com/show-twitz-rufa-mae-quinto-goodbye-showbiz-na |title=Show Twitz: Rufa Mae Quinto, goodbye showbiz na? |publisher=Pinoy Parazzi |date=2010-07-12 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> The movie was shown at the [[Cultural Center of the Philippines]] more than twice,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abante.com.ph/issue/mar2811/istayl03.htm |title=Abante Online |publisher=Abante.com.ph |date=2011-03-28 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at the [[University of the Philippines Diliman|U.P. Diliman]] Film Center and [[University of the Philippines Los Ba\u00f1os|U.P. Los Ba\u00f1os]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clickthecity.com/events/details.php?id=10722 |title=Ganap na Babae (Garden of Eve) @ ClickTheCity.com Events |publisher=Clickthecity.com |date=2011-03-10 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at the [[National Commission for Culture and the Arts]] (NCCA),<ref>{{cite web|author=Polixenia Klein Robles |url=http://www.metrokelan.com/movies-and-shows/ganap-na-babae_i15747 |title=Ganap na Babae \u2013 Metrokelan \u2013 Current Events in the Philippines 2015 |publisher=Metrokelan |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/175700 |title=GARDEN OF EVE (Ganap Na Babae) Special Double Screening in SALT LAKE CITY, UTAH |publisher=Brownpapertickets.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> and to a sold out [[New York City|New York]] screening, where it bagged a SoHo International Film Festival NYC Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/mobile/guide/indie/8045/ganap-na-babae-bags-soho-international-film-festival-nyc-award |title=Ganap na Babae bags SoHo International Film Festival NYC Award &#124; PEP.ph Mobile: The Number One Site for Philippine Showbiz |publisher=Pep.ph |date=2011-04-25 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> The film was honored as [[6th Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival|Cinemalaya 2010]]'s opening and closing film <ref>{{cite web |url=http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20100722-282458/Three-Eves |title=Three Eves \u2013 INQUIRER.net, Philippine News for Filipinos |publisher=Opinion.inquirer.net |date=2010-07-22 |accessdate=2015-05-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518095655/http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20100722-282458/Three-Eves |archivedate=2015-05-18 }}</ref> and has won other international<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1690126/awards</ref> and local <ref>{{cite web|url=http://hubo.asia/ani-ng-dangal-harvest-of-honors-2012-event/ |title=ANI NG DANGAL (Harvest of Honors) 2012 Event \u00ab HUBO Productions |publisher=Hubo.asia |date=2012-02-29 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> recognition including the Harvest of Honor ([[Ani ng Dangal]]) award conferred by the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (NCCA) under the Office of the President of the Philippines.\n\n\"Minsan may Isang Puta\" became viral in social media in 2012 with over 40,000 likes and shares <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=435769746453511&set=a.164261513604337.35407.138846849479137&type=1&theater&notif_t=photo_comment |title=Reid Bacongco \u2013 Timeline Photos |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> and has been consistently Definitely Filipino's Popular All Time article <ref>{{cite web|author=Ms. Mike Portes |url=http://definitelyfilipino.com/blog/2013/09/09/minsan-may-isang-puta-2007/ |title=Minsan may Isang Puta (2007) \u00bb Definitely Filipino\u2122 |publisher=Definitelyfilipino.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> that inspired creative amateur productions in Filipino and Theater subjects in High Schools and Universities over the years.\n\n== Publications ==\nThe royalties from the author's sole-authored books, \u201cThe Dove Files\u201d and \"Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba Pa\" paperbacks at Barnes and Noble Online, went to two \"Project Malasakit scholars\". A Typhoon Yolanda survivor who graduated Cum Laude from the University of the Philippines Visayas on June 2019 and passed the CPA licensure exam. <ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttps://www.gmanetwork.com/news/lifestyle/hobbiesandactivities/698958/yolanda-survivor-from-tacloban-graduates-cum-laude-from-up-visayas/story/ |title=Yolanda survivor from Tacloban graduates cum Laude from UP Visayas</ref> and the daughter of a late cancer victim who graduated Cum Laude on April 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://karapatria.com/report_2013.html#graduates |title=Accomplishment Report (February 2013 \u2013 February 2014) &#124; Project Malasakit by Kara David |publisher=Karapatria.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> the rest was paid forward to baby Mark who underwent a liver transplant in March 2013.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Philippine short stories]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox book\n| name          = Minsan may Isang Puta (short story)\n| image         =\n| caption       = \n| author        = Mike Portes\n| language      = [[Filipino language|Filipino]]\n| genre         = [[Fictional biographies]]\n| published     = *April 30, 2004, Peyups.com\n* December, 2011 Mismo Magazine (U.A.E.)\n*July 16, 2012, The Dove Files<ref>{{cite book|last1=Portes|first1=Mike|title=The Dove Files |date=July 16, 2012|publisher=CreateSpace Publishing|isbn=978-1-4774-3185-6|page=136|url=https://www.amazon.com/The-Dove-Files-Mike-Portes/dp/1477431853}}</ref>\n*Nov 22, 2014, Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba pa\n<ref>{{cite book|last1=Portes|first1=Mike|title=Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba pa|date=November 22, 2014|publisher=CreateSpace Publishing|isbn=978-1-5031-3504-8|page=112|url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/minsan-may-isang-puta-mike-portes/1120821316?ean=9781503135048}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Minsan may Isang Puta''' is an allegory in Filipino, written by Ms. Mike Portes <ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://hubo.asia/tag/minsan-may-isang-puta |title=Minsan May Isang Puta \u00ab HUBO Productions |publisher=Hubo.asia |date=2012-10-22 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> in 2004 and was modified in 2007.\n\n== Summary ==\nA woman bares her soul to her listener. As she shares her pain and unravels herself, she becomes more than the perceived prostitute but a survivor and a mother who is both familiar and forgotten.\n\n\"...a short piece that uses a first-person narrative technique that speaks directly to its reader. The voice is even pedestrian that in its familiar tone the reader is simply drawn to it. The voice simply asks that you listen as if an old friend or relative is about to tell a story. It is a story that found thousands of listening ears since it first appeared in 2004. The story is at once familiar yet enigmatic. In \u201cre-telling the truth through the words of a loving mother and by using sex as an impulse zone\u201d is perhaps what makes it fresh, intimate and endearing.'' (\"When Doves Cry\", October 22, 2012)<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n== Film Adaptation and Reception ==\n\n'''Minsan may Isang Puta''' won a film grant in 2010 in the [[multiperspectivity|multi-narrative]] indie film: \"Ganap na Babae\" (International title: Garden of Eve).\n\nMs. [[Mercedes Cabral]] in her role in the screenplay of \"Minsan may Isang Puta\" was praised by local media.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pinoyparazzi.com/show-twitz-rufa-mae-quinto-goodbye-showbiz-na |title=Show Twitz: Rufa Mae Quinto, goodbye showbiz na? |publisher=Pinoy Parazzi |date=2010-07-12 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> The movie was shown at the [[Cultural Center of the Philippines]] more than twice,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abante.com.ph/issue/mar2811/istayl03.htm |title=Abante Online |publisher=Abante.com.ph |date=2011-03-28 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at the [[University of the Philippines Diliman|U.P. Diliman]] Film Center and [[University of the Philippines Los Ba\u00f1os|U.P. Los Ba\u00f1os]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clickthecity.com/events/details.php?id=10722 |title=Ganap na Babae (Garden of Eve) @ ClickTheCity.com Events |publisher=Clickthecity.com |date=2011-03-10 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at the [[National Commission for Culture and the Arts]] (NCCA),<ref>{{cite web|author=Polixenia Klein Robles |url=http://www.metrokelan.com/movies-and-shows/ganap-na-babae_i15747 |title=Ganap na Babae \u2013 Metrokelan \u2013 Current Events in the Philippines 2015 |publisher=Metrokelan |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> at [[Salt Lake City]], [[Utah]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/175700 |title=GARDEN OF EVE (Ganap Na Babae) Special Double Screening in SALT LAKE CITY, UTAH |publisher=Brownpapertickets.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> and to a sold out [[New York City|New York]] screening, where it bagged a SoHo International Film Festival NYC Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/mobile/guide/indie/8045/ganap-na-babae-bags-soho-international-film-festival-nyc-award |title=Ganap na Babae bags SoHo International Film Festival NYC Award &#124; PEP.ph Mobile: The Number One Site for Philippine Showbiz |publisher=Pep.ph |date=2011-04-25 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> The film was honored as [[6th Cinemalaya Independent Film Festival|Cinemalaya 2010]]'s opening and closing film <ref>{{cite web |url=http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20100722-282458/Three-Eves |title=Three Eves \u2013 INQUIRER.net, Philippine News for Filipinos |publisher=Opinion.inquirer.net |date=2010-07-22 |accessdate=2015-05-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518095655/http://opinion.inquirer.net/inquireropinion/columns/view/20100722-282458/Three-Eves |archivedate=2015-05-18 }}</ref> and has won other international<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1690126/awards</ref> and local <ref>{{cite web|url=http://hubo.asia/ani-ng-dangal-harvest-of-honors-2012-event/ |title=ANI NG DANGAL (Harvest of Honors) 2012 Event \u00ab HUBO Productions |publisher=Hubo.asia |date=2012-02-29 |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> recognition including the Harvest of Honor ([[Ani ng Dangal]]) award conferred by the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (NCCA) under the Office of the President of the Philippines.\n\n\"Minsan may Isang Puta\" became viral in social media in 2012 with over 40,000 likes and shares <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=435769746453511&set=a.164261513604337.35407.138846849479137&type=1&theater&notif_t=photo_comment |title=Reid Bacongco \u2013 Timeline Photos |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> and has been consistently Definitely Filipino's Popular All Time article <ref>{{cite web|author=Ms. Mike Portes |url=http://definitelyfilipino.com/blog/2013/09/09/minsan-may-isang-puta-2007/ |title=Minsan may Isang Puta (2007) \u00bb Definitely Filipino\u2122 |publisher=Definitelyfilipino.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> that inspired creative amateur productions in Filipino and Theater subjects in High Schools and Universities over the years.\n\n== Publications ==\nThe royalties from the author's sole-authored books, \u201cThe Dove Files\u201d and \"Minsan may Isang Puta at Iba Pa\" paperbacks at Barnes and Noble Online, went to two \"Project Malasakit scholars\". A Typhoon Yolanda survivor who graduated Cum Laude from the University of the Philippines Visayas on June 2019 and and passed the CPA licensure exam. <ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttps://www.gmanetwork.com/news/lifestyle/hobbiesandactivities/698958/yolanda-survivor-from-tacloban-graduates-cum-laude-from-up-visayas/story/ |title=Yolanda survivor from Tacloban graduates cum Laude from UP Visayas</ref> and the daughter of a late cancer victim who graduated Cum Laude on April 2013,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://karapatria.com/report_2013.html#graduates |title=Accomplishment Report (February 2013 \u2013 February 2014) &#124; Project Malasakit by Kara David |publisher=Karapatria.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-12}}</ref> the rest was paid forward to baby Mark who underwent a liver transplant in March 2013.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Philippine short stories]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minsan_may_isang_puta"}
{"title_page": "Future Nostalgia Tour", "text_new": "{{Infobox concert\n| concert_tour_name = Future Nostalgia Tour\n| image = Future Nostalgia Tour poster.png\n| image_size = 220\n| landscape = yes\n| caption = Promotional poster for the tour\n| artist = [[Dua Lipa]]\n| location = Europe\n| type = \n| album = ''[[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|Future Nostalgia]]''\n| start_date = {{Start date|2021|01|03|df=yes}}\n| end_date = {{End date|2021|02|16|df=yes}}\n| number_of_legs = \n| number_of_shows = 21\n| support_acts = [[Lolo Zoua\u00ef]]<br>DJ Buck Betty\n| last_tour = [[List of Dua Lipa concert tours#The Self-Titled Tour (2017-2018)|The Self-Titled Tour]]<br>(2017\u201318)\n| this_tour ='''Future Nostalgia Tour'''<br>(2021)\n| next_tour = \n}}\n\nThe '''Future Nostalgia Tour''' is the upcoming second [[concert tour]] by English singer [[Dua Lipa]]. It will be launched in support of her second studio album [[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|''Future Nostalgia'']] (2020) and will visit Europe. It is scheduled to begin on 3 January 2021 in Newcastle, England at the [[Utilita Arena]] and conclude on 16 February 2021 in Madrid, Spain at the [[WiZink Center]]. The tour was first announced in December 2019, consisting of dates in Europe.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-announces-2020-uk-arena-tour-and-shares-new-album-title-2582524|title=Dua Lipa announces 2020 UK arena tour and shares new album title|last=Reilly|first=Nick|date=2 December 2019|website=[[NME]]|access-date=2 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nIn October 2019, Lipa announced \"[[Don't Start Now (Dua Lipa song)|Don't Start Now]]\", the lead single from her upcoming second album [[Future Nostalgia (Dua Lipa album)|''Future Nostalgia'']] (2020).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dua-lipa-shares-new-song-dont-start-now-listen/|title=Dua Lipa Shares New Song \"Don't Start Now\": Listen|last=Strauss|first=Matthew|date=31 October 2019|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|access-date=2 December 2019}}</ref> The album title was then announced on 1 December, with the European leg of a new arena tour announced the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-2020-tour-920105/|title=Dua Lipa Announces 'Fresh and Futuristic' New Album \u2018Future Nostalgia\u2019|last=Zemler|first=Emily|date=2 December 2019|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=2 December 2019}}</ref> On 27 January 2020, it was announced that Lipa would be performing at the 2020 [[Radio 1's Big Weekend]] in Dundee.<ref name=\"bigweekend\">{{cite web |last1=Reilly |first1=Nick |title=Harry Styles, Dua Lipa and Biffy Clyro among first names for Radio 1\u2019s Big Weekend in Dundee |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/radio-1-big-weekend-harry-styles-dua-lipa-biffy-clyro-dundee-line-up-tickets-2601445 |website=[[NME]] |publisher=[[Warner Music Group]] |accessdate=23 February 2020 |date=27 January 2020}}</ref> In the following month, dates in Liverpool and Nottingham were added to the tour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/dua-lipa-has-added-two-new-uk-dates-to-her-arena-tour-2613193|title=Dua Lipa has added two new UK dates to her arena tour|last=Neale|first=Matthew|date=21 February 2020|website=[[NME]]|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref> On 12 March, Lipa's performance at the 2020 [[Glastonbury Festival]] was announced.<ref name=\"glastonbury\">{{cite news|last1=Savage|first1=Mark|title=Glastonbury 2020 reveals line-up amid uncertainty over coronavirus|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-51860319|accessdate=13 March 2020|work=[[BBC News]]|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Postponement ===\nOn 23 March, Lipa announced that the tour would be postponed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. Rescheduled dates were confirmed the next morning at 10:00 [[Greenwich Mean Time|GMT]].<ref name=\"livenation\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|title=Dua Lipa Tickets|last=|first=|date=24 March 2020|website=[[Live Nation]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324104559/https://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|archive-date=24 March 2020|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Tour dates ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of concerts, showing date, city, country, venue, opening acts, tickets sold, number of available tickets and gross revenue<ref>Dates:\n\n*Original: {{Cite web|url=https://www.dualipa.com/tour/|title=Tour - Dua Lipa|last=|first=|date=12 February 2020|website=dualipa.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214173234/https://www.dualipa.com/tour/|archive-date=14 February 2020|access-date=14 February 2020}}\n*Rescheduled: {{Cite web|url=https://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|title=Dua Lipa Tickets|last=|first=|date=24 March 2020|website=[[Live Nation]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324104559/https://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/dua-lipa-tickets|archive-date=24 March 2020|access-date=24 March 2020}}\n</ref><ref>Opening acts:\n*Lolo Zoua\u00ef and DJ Buck Betty: {{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/DUALIPA/status/1216725081860251650|title=Taking my girlfriendsssss on TOUR!!! We\u2019re excited to see youuuuu|last=Lipa|first=Dua|date=13 January 2020|via=[[Twitter]]|access-date=13 January 2020}}\n*Dagny: {{Cite web|url=https://www.livenation.no/show/1295142/dua-lipa-future-nostalgia-tour/oslo/2020-05-13/no|title=Kj\u00f8p billetter for Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia Tour p\u00e5 Oslo Spektrum p\u00e5 13.05.2020|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Live Nation]]|language=no|trans-title=Buy tickets for Dua Lipa: Future Nostalgia Tour at Oslo Spektrum on 13.05.2020|access-date=7 March 2020}}\n</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"|Date\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|City\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"|Country\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: